I've tried several other flashcard apps, including Quizlet and AnkiDroid, but this app is by far the easiest one to use for creating and managing flashcards. It's not as advanced as AnkiDroid, but I prefer the simplicity of this app which resembles old-fashioned cards. You don't have to deal with extra settings, like timers.  I create all the flashcards on my computer and sync them to my tablet. You are able to adjust the font type and size in the app, and there are more advanced settings on the website, such as changing the text's color or adding images. The "quick editor" tool on the website allows you to manage and edit the flashcards very easily. You can change the order of the cards, delete, add, etc.  While viewing the flashcards, you also have the ability to mark which ones you got right and are easy to you, so they disappear from the set until you click "reset." This helps me to focus on the cards that I really need to study. And best of all, you can download other people's flashcards for the same subject! Even though Quizlet is quite popular for this, this app still has a large, impressive collection.  Flashcard Machine is worth the money, great for long-term use.
